<br>
Any terminals located on '''Level 959''' are logged on to [[Phenomenon 2|BACK-NET]] and its websites with an account titled "NOW-YOU-KNOW" and a profile photo of an image of the level, meaning any posts or comments created will transmit '''Nonpentennism''' as hapless wanderers gaze at the unassuming profile. It is possible to log out of the accounts, but doing so will permanently sever the connection to BACK-NET. These terminals are, unfortunately, the only way to conduct interlevel communication, as devices like walkie-talkies and mobile phones lose connection once brought into the level.

Roughly 1 in 30 individuals plagued with '''Nonpentennism''' are deemed "Long Haulers", in which either the stages of the infohazard take course over several months instead of one week, or stage progression halts at the second or third stage.<ref>Their death is instead through natural causes as they never enter the later, more damning stages of the infohazard.</ref> Long Haulers are the primary source of information and testimony regarding '''Level 959'''. They often seclude themselves from larger Backrooms societies in fear of accidentally spreading the infohazard or being weaponized by certain groups. Some, particularly those who have ended up on [[Level 477]] and [[Level 570]], have founded an organization dedicated to the research of '''Level 959''' and its core peril.

<div class="header">Entities</div>
Certain entities are also susceptible to '''Nonpentennism''', though it is unclear exactly which ones. Accounts depict the growls of [[Entity 8|Hounds]] to the mumbling of [[Entity 9|Facelings]] bouncing around the walls of '''Level 959'''. Speculations regarding which entities succumb to '''Nonpentennism''' suggest it may spare beings below a certain IQ threshold, affect only humanoid entities of the Backrooms, or be entirely unpredictable, with no clear pattern of susceptibility.

<div class="header">Settlements</div>
<div class="log">
<div class="log-container">
[[File:Finallyitworks.png|300px|center]]
<br><hr><br>
Comprising a handful of stranded Long Haulers who ended up on [[Level 477]] and [[Level 570]], the '''Society of the Tresorwächter'''<ref>German for "The Vault Keepers".</ref> is a small group dedicated to the documentation, research, and safeguarding of '''Level 959''' and '''Nonpentennism'''. The group was founded five years after the level's discovery on November 6, 2020, amassing a total of 266 split between the two given levels. Both their settlements are secluded to outsiders and even barricaded, adorned with stark warning signs. They keep secretive ties with the [[M.E.G.|Major Explorer Group]] and Kauer.

Besides private documentation and public safekeeping, the core tenet of the '''Tresorwächter''' that led to its foundation are that Long Haulers bear untold levels of destructive potential that militaristic groups like [[Republic of Aurielle|Aurielle]], [[Duchy of Cascada|Cascada]] and the [[User:ArbiTraitor/AEG_Rewrite|Anti-Entity Group]] would exploit. The group's seclusion helps to shield the members against foreign propaganda, but fears circulate about those not in the group, as they could be less conservative of their destructive potential due to weakened rational thought. 
</div>
</div>

