<div style="background:linear-gradient(to bottom, #FFFFFF 34px, #266C91 1px);background-size:40px 35px;"><div style="background:#C13720;margin-left:39px;"><div style="background:linear-gradient(to bottom, #FFFFFF 34px, #266C91 1px);background-size:35px 35px;line-height:35px;margin-left:1px;"><div style="background:linear-gradient(to bottom, #FFFFFF 34px, #266C91 1px);background-size:35px 35px;line-height:35px;margin-left:5px;margin-right:5px;"><br><span style="margin-left:35px"><span style="color:black; font-size:20px; font-family:Jua;">

The fact that we long haulers even exist is something that terrifies me just as much as Level 959 itself. Why does the level purposely keep a few of its victims alive to tell the tale of its horrors? Our existence and perserverance is purposeful, and the truth may be wicked. Level 959 spares a handful to slay thousands more. The Backrooms itself is weaponizing us, possibly to rid itself of us pesky humans explaining and colonizing places we were never meant to set foot on.<br><br>Tresorwachter is at best a band-aid solution to what will come and merely delays what is inevitable. For every long hauler who realizes their situation and finds refuge in our cause, there could be tens more who skip past us, who never even set foot on 477 and 570, never knowing about our existence and end up on the wrong side of history.<br><br>Say, one of us manages to convince the Anti-Entity Group of their potential, they will simply be scoffed at. But that will change if one becomes ten, and plans start setting in motion. Soon, it's not just the AEG, but also Aurielle, Cascada, hell, even the MEG could turn their backs on us.<br><br>We are like nuclear weapons in the Frontrooms, machinations too powerful and too destructive to be used in war, and only as empty threats. But even if that happens, and wars are actually prevented due to our destructive potential, the AEG could be using us to wipe out entire entity populations in mere sweeps.<br><br>If Level 959 simply killed off all of its victims, it would just simply be redacted from the Database and will only slowly chip away at the human population in the Backrooms. So, to kill thousands and perhaps millions more, you have to save a handful.<br><br>It is not a matter of if, but when. These militaristic giants will eventually find out about our destructive potential. We can only hope that we will too powerful to be fielded in combat, that our presence actually prevents wars from breaking out. Founding our little group may only delay what's to come, but there's no better way we can approach this.<br><br>But let's try to focus on the now, to keep Level 959 from the public while it is still feasible. For now, we can enjoy these times of peace and order while they last.<br><br>-Imogen Rachel S. Lexington


