=== Entrances===
*If one hasn't entered '''Level 959''' during the five-day grace period of Nonpentennism, they will noclip through the floor of their respective level;
*Noclipping through the pipes in [[Level 477]]'s Nexus will lead one here;
*Holes in the floor in [[Level 198]] will lead one here;
*Waiting for long enough without ordering in [[Level 167]] will prompt the voice to recommend a "special offer". Once accepted, the voice will prompt the wanderer to look behind, revealing a hallway transitioning to this level;
*A Porsche in [[Level Tau]] will noclip one here once entered;
*Traversing a dark hallway in The Station of [[Level 369]] will lead one here;
*A dark hallway in [[Level 266]] will lead here, particularly to the second floor;
*On [[Level 217]], using a computer and typing out "I do not want to know" sends one here. This includes variations of the phrase as well as translations in other languages;
*Going through a dark red door in [[Level 208]] will lead to this level;
*Noclipping through the floor in one of the buildings on [[Level 258]] will lead one here;
*Entering a door with 959 in Roman numerals<ref>CMLIX.</ref> on it in [[Level 917]] will lead to this level; and
*Unknown factors in [[Level 311]].

===Exits ===
It is notable to mention that all exits in '''Level 959''' are exceedingly rare.

*Noclipping through a large organ<ref>Refers to the instrument.</ref> will send one to [[Level 447]];
*Entering a door with the number 477 on it will lead to [[Level 477]];
*Random noclipping can send one to [[Level 960]], but its inconsistent;
*Entering a spacious and stylistically deviant space will transition to [[Level 570]];
*Descending a staircase from the first floor leads one to [[Level 502]];
*Diving into a pitfall filled with water, then resurfacing sends one to [[Level 205]] or [[Level 102]];
*Noclipping through any of the windows that display this pitfall sends one to [[Level 43]]; and
*The level might fade into the first sublevel of [[Level REDACTED]]. Upon entering, one will be relieved of Nonpentennism and their memories regarding '''Level 959''' will be fully wiped out. This is one of the only "cures" to the dreadful infohazard, ''but at what cost''?

